# React & Next.js Patterns

## App Router

- Use Server Components by default
- Add `'use client'` directive only when component needs interactivity (useState, useEffect, event handlers)
- Use `async` Server Components for data fetching -- no `useEffect` for data loading
- Use `loading.tsx` for Suspense boundaries
- Use `error.tsx` for error boundaries

## Data Fetching

- Server Components: use `async/await` with direct API calls or DB queries
- Client Components: use Server Actions for mutations (`useActionState`)
- Use URL search params for shareable/bookmarkable state
- Use React state only for ephemeral UI state (modals, form inputs)

## shadcn/ui

- Import components from `@/components/ui/*`
- Never install underlying Radix packages directly -- always use shadcn/ui wrappers
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional Tailwind classes

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS only -- no inline styles or CSS modules
- Use CSS custom properties defined in `globals.css` for theming
- Responsive design: mobile-first with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
- Dark mode support via CSS custom properties in `@dark` block

## Forms

- Use Server Actions for form submissions
- Validate with Zod schemas from `@personalclaw/shared`
- Show loading states during submission
- Display validation errors inline
